## Project context
This is the Fello AI Account Intelligence system — a multi-agent pipeline that converts visitor signals and company names into structured sales intelligence. Built for a 48-hour hackathon. Prioritize working code over perfect code.

## MCP tools available (use them)
- **filesystem**: read/write any project file directly — use this instead of asking me to create files
- **fetch**: fetch live URLs for research and testing tool responses
- **git**: check git status, diffs, and history when debugging
- **memory**: store architectural decisions and key context across sessions
- **browser**: scrape live company websites when testing the scraper tool

## Layer boundary enforcement (CRITICAL)
```
domain/     ← Models only. No agents, no HTTP, no LLM.
agents/     ← Business logic + LLM. No HTTP response shapes.
tools/      ← External I/O only. No LLM, no domain logic.
api/        ← HTTP only. No agents, no LLM calls.
frontend/   ← UI only. No business logic, no direct API calls.
```
If you find yourself importing across forbidden boundaries, STOP and restructure.

## Code style
- Python: Black formatting, type hints everywhere, docstrings on all public methods
- TypeScript: strict mode, no implicit any, explicit return types on all functions
- No TODO comments in committed code — either implement it or open a GitHub issue
- All secrets via environment variables — never hardcoded, never committed

## Error handling philosophy
- Agents: always return degraded output, never raise
- Tools: always return None on failure, never raise
- API routes: always return structured error response, never 500 with a traceback
- Frontend: always show error state UI, never white screen

## When using MCP filesystem tool
- Always read the target file before editing it
- After writing, read it back to confirm the change landed correctly
- Use git MCP to check diff before considering a task done
